We also computed the feature importance scores for the baseline decision tree and found that the top three most important features were N stages, progesterone status, and Grade. In the later section, we compare the important features identified by our best model and baseline model."

"
The issues highlighted in the book are closely related to many of the topics discussed in our class. The development of these systems is top-down from a policy-making perspective, often implemented by some tech contractors, without systematically surveying and understanding the community needs and their relationship and interaction with the street-level bureaucrats. For example, in the first case study, the system developed by IBM for automating the welfare system in Indiana makes the assumption that cases can be broken down into tasks, which can be managed and tracked individually by newly-trained workers behind the screen. It almost completely circumvented the case workers, who used to evaluate the case holistically and offer assistance, many of whom got displaced because of the automated system. However, the system was not able to replace the caseworkers and, in many cases, its malfunctioning had a direct negative impact on members of the community who are in urgent need of help. The Omega Young case is a good example, where the system error denied her medical benefits and food stamps, even though she was terminally ill. Six-year-old Sophie, who was suffering from severe developmental problems and relied on Medicaid benefits to stay alive, was kicked off Medicaid by the system because she “failed to cooperate” with no immediate option to appeal. Many of these issues have caused devastating consequences and an unnecessary amount of stress to victims. They could be prevented by using a participatory design approach where the community, case-workers and policymakers can communicate their needs and feedback to the technology designer. Frameworks like participatory design advocate for a human-centered approach and view the users as resourceful and independent agents. However, in the Indiana public welfare system case, the administration’s objective is to develop a brand-new system to reduce the State's operating costs."

When using the language model's learned graph representation as input, the accuracy of shallow GNN on downstream NLP tasks reflects the level of mutual information between the model's hidden representation of text and the target syntactic properties. To investigate if these graphs also capture the grammatical structure of a sentence, we can leverage community detection algorithms to cluster the words (nodes) and assess how well the clusters align with the grammatical relations between words.

"This work fits into a long line of interpretability research. Previous study attempted to uncover the linguistic properties encoded in language models through probing. The probing approach measures the mutual information between a model's hidden representations of words and their linguistic properties in a sentence. However, these works ignore the explicit connection between words established by the attention mechanism. Another branch of works interprets the emergent linguistic ability of language models by analyzing their learnt attention pattern. Recent works suggest attention alone cannot explain the performance of transformer models. My project will bridge the above two approaches by analyzing both learnt word features and sentence structure (attention) using a graph neural network."

Delete 10 words or phrases from the following paragraph that don't contribute much to its meaning, but keep readability:
"In conclusion, Aristotle hastily generalizes that the middling sort will develop affection, reason, and moderation, but these characteristics are less accurate. The cultural and socio-economic diversity has made it challenging to summarize the features of a particular group. We need various criteria, not limited to one’s class or wealth, to determine if an individual or a group of individuals is suitable to rule. Additionally, Aristotle’s succinct model is not highly adaptable to the complex modern society. The mixed constitution is intended to incorporate the strengths of oligarchies and democracies, but the combination will also introduce new problems. The quality of laws depends on the quality of a regime. Under a defective regime, laws will digress from moderation and allow room for abuse of power, resulting in factional conflicts, exploitation, and oppression. Although Aristotle believes that a middle class polity is stable and moderate, this form of government may not fulfill its potential beyond the scope of his book."

Delete 10 words or phrases from the following paragraph that don't contribute much to its meaning, but keep readability:
"Second, unrestricted monarchial power guarantees that subjects can enjoy basic civil liberties. One’s submission to a commonwealth consists of both obligation and liberty. Individuals in society should acknowledge the necessity to fulfill the contractual obligation and understand the mutual relationship between obligation and liberty. Due to their “natural passions,” men tend to seek “liberty and dominion over others” (Leviathan Chap. XVII, p. 106). If someone is reluctant to limit his or her absolute liberty and exploits others with unchecked power, then people will be cast back to the “miserable condition of war” (Leviathan Chap. XVII, p. 106). To maintain peace among members, all must obey the Second Law of Nature which requires a man to “lay down” some of his rights, be “contented with” limited liberty (Leviathan Chap. XIV, p. 80), and meet certain obligations to avoid conflicts. The obligations are the prerequisites for civil liberties that subjects acquire once their lives and possessions are safe from threats. Liberty is thus the opposite of “an unbridled license” (Rousseau, Second Discourse, p. 32). For subjects to truly enjoy their civil liberties, the sovereign must make sure that the subjects abide by the civil law. Fear thus comes into play because “covenants without the sword are but words, and of no strength to secure a man at all” (Leviathan Chap. XVII, p. 106). The sovereign power keeps subjects “in awe”, and “tie[s] them by fear of punishment to the performance of their covenants” (Leviathan Chap. XVII, p. 106). Without fear, subjects will think that they have the freedom to disregard the sovereign’s command and disobey the law, which could do harm to other law-abiding citizens and cause internal dissension. People’s revolutions to “shake off the yoke” will also make them vulnerable to attack from other countries “who simply make their chains heavier” (Rousseau, Second Discourse, p. 32). Therefore, fear promotes civil liberty by rendering the danger of breaking laws. Although fear deters some actions of people, it is consistent with liberty. Subjects still have freedom from obligation. “All actions which men do in commonwealths for fear of the law are actions which the doers had liberty to omit” (Leviathan Chap. XXI, p. 136). Subjects are coerced to obey civil law out of fear, yet they still have the liberty to disobey."

Delete 10 words or phrases from the following paragraph that don't contribute much to its meaning, but keep readability:
"In addition, Mill refutes Rousseau’s claim that the minority should obey the majority. The freedom of opinion and the expression of opinion is necessary to the “mental well-being of mankind on which all their other well-being depends” (On Liberty, Chap. II, p. 50). The debates are not zero-sum games and the government should reconcile the disputes instead of muting one side. As one voice prevails, the others should not trail off into silence. Instead, the minority and the majority should share equal rights to deliver their ideas. Filtering outliers violates the principle of equality, contravenes the spirit of democracy, and undermines the foundation of government. Even if there is only one nonconformist, it is unjustified to silence that one dissenter (On Liberty, Chap. II, p. 16). Furthermore, Mill recognizes the value of minority views regardless of their validity. If a heretical view is correct and the popular belief is wrong, people will lose the opportunity of “exchanging error for truth” (On Liberty, Chap. II, p. 16). Even though a minority view may be wrong, discussing it will make the truth more conspicuous, impressive, and convincing. In general, respecting niche markets of ideas will conserve human intelligence, stimulate scholarly communication, and advance scientific development. In political spheres, having open dialogues develops individuals’ critical faculties and independent thinking abilities. When participants attend assemblies, they debate, vote, and legislate more rationally, with more concern for the common good, which will benefit society in the long run."

Although this project was theory focused, I conducted extensive numerical experiments to better understand these algorithms. We summarized our results in late August and are preparing for submissions."

"Various strategies have been recently reported to augment the anti-tumor efficacy of NK cells. Many of these strategies target endogenous NK cells. Genetic engineering approaches have been also reported for adoptive NK therapy, namely the generation of CAR-NK cells, however, these approaches have limitations from the developmental and safety perspective. Among non-genetic engineering approaches to improve adoptive NK transfer, pre-activation and expansion with cytokines is the most popular strategy. However, the activated NK cells need constant cytokine infusions to maintain their activity in-vivo which may lead to off-target adverse effects.  Co-administration of monoclonal antibodies to induce ADCC is also a widely used approach but relies on tumor-targeting for NK activation. Here, we present an alternate strategy to constantly stimulate NK cells that is scalable, rapid and can synergize with current priming methods in the clinic. MACE represents a modular platform that can be functionalized with surface antibodies or ligands targeting various receptors on the NK cell, thus allowing us to modulate cellular activation status. We designed MACE to target NK receptors of the NCR family and deliver constant activating signals to the cell. We highlight that the mechanism of this signaling is driven by localized microscale receptor clustering, which MACE can induce due to their unique geometry. It was recently reported that the mechanical force on lymphocyte receptors can greatly affect downstream signaling which may also be contribute to the ability of MACE to induce greater signaling as compared to free antibodies. We also report screening data for a variety of NK receptors for adhesion and activation, which may further the understanding of basic NK biology."

Co-administration of monoclonal antibodies to induce ADCC is also widely used but relies on tumor-targeting for NK activation. Here, we present alternate strategy to stimulate NK cells that is scalable, rapid and can synergize with current priming methods in clinic. MACE represents a modular platform that can be functionalized with surface antibodies or ligands targeting receptors on NK cell, allowing us to modulate activation status. We designed MACE to target NK receptors of NCR family and deliver constant activating signals to cell. Mechanism of signaling driven by localized receptor clustering, which MACE induces due to their unique geometry. Recently reported mechanical force on lymphocyte receptors can greatly affect downstream signaling contributing to MACE's ability to induce greater signaling than free antibodies. Screening data reported for variety of NK receptors for adhesion and activation, furthering understanding of basic NK biology.

info.paragraph: Various strategies have been recently reported to augment the anti-tumor efficacy of NK cells. Many of these strategies target endogenous NK cells. Genetic engineering approaches have been also reported for adoptive NK therapy, namely the generation of CAR-NK cells, however, these approaches have limitations from the developmental and safety perspective. Among non-genetic engineering approaches to improve adoptive NK transfer, pre-activation and expansion with cytokines is the most popular strategy. However, the activated NK cells need constant cytokine infusions to maintain their activity in-vivo which may lead to off-target adverse effects.  Co-administration of monoclonal antibodies to induce ADCC is also a widely used approach but relies on tumor-targeting for NK activation. Here, we present an alternate strategy to constantly stimulate NK cells that is scalable, rapid and can synergize with current priming methods in the clinic. MACE represents a modular platform that can be functionalized with surface antibodies or ligands targeting various receptors on the NK cell, thus allowing us to modulate cellular activation status. We designed MACE to target NK receptors of the NCR family and deliver constant activating signals to the cell. We highlight that the mechanism of this signaling is driven by localized microscale receptor clustering, which MACE can induce due to their unique geometry. It was recently reported that the mechanical force on lymphocyte receptors can greatly affect downstream signaling which may also be contribute to the ability of MACE to induce greater signaling as compared to free antibodies. We also report screening data for a variety of NK receptors for adhesion and activation, which may further the understanding of basic NK biology.

Delete 10 words or phrases from the following paragraph that don't contribute much to its meaning, but keep readability:
"Natural Killer (NK) cell therapies have recently emerged as a potential therapeutic approach against various cancers. Their efficacy however is limited by low cell persistence and eventual cell anergy. Current approaches to sustain NK cell persistence in vivo include genetic modification or activation via pre- or co-administration of supporting cytokines or antibodies. Such supporting therapies exhibit limited efficacy in vivo in part due to the reversal of their effect within the immunosuppressive tumor microenvironment. Here, we report a material-based approach to address this challenge. Specifically, we describe the use of polymeric micropatches as a platform for sustained, targeted activation of NK cells, an approach referred to as Microparticles as Cell Engagers (MACE). PLGA micropatches 4-8 m in diameter and surface-modified with NK targeting antibodies exhibit strong adhesion to NK cells and induce their activation even without the need of any co-administered cytokines. The activation induced by MACE is greater than that induced by nanoparticles, thus attesting to the unique role of MACE geometry in the activation of NK cells. MACE-NK cells remained viable and exhibited trans-endothelial migration and anti-tumor activity in vitro. MACE-NK cells also demonstrated anti-tumor efficacy in a mouse melanoma lung metastasis model. Overall, MACE offers a simple, scalable and effective way of activating NK cells and represents an attractive platform to improve efficacy of NK therapy."

MACE induces greater activation than nanoparticles, attesting to the unique role of MACE geometry. MACE-NK cells remain viable and exhibit anti-tumor activity. MACE offers a scalable way of activating NK cells and represents an attractive platform to improve NK therapy.

info.paragraph: Natural Killer (NK) cell therapies have recently emerged as a potential therapeutic approach against various cancers. Their efficacy however is limited by low cell persistence and eventual cell anergy. Current approaches to sustain NK cell persistence in vivo include genetic modification or activation via pre- or co-administration of supporting cytokines or antibodies. Such supporting therapies exhibit limited efficacy in vivo in part due to the reversal of their effect within the immunosuppressive tumor microenvironment. Here, we report a material-based approach to address this challenge. Specifically, we describe the use of polymeric micropatches as a platform for sustained, targeted activation of NK cells, an approach referred to as Microparticles as Cell Engagers (MACE). PLGA micropatches 4-8 m in diameter and surface-modified with NK targeting antibodies exhibit strong adhesion to NK cells and induce their activation even without the need of any co-administered cytokines. The activation induced by MACE is greater than that induced by nanoparticles, thus attesting to the unique role of MACE geometry in the activation of NK cells. MACE-NK cells remained viable and exhibited trans-endothelial migration and anti-tumor activity in vitro. MACE-NK cells also demonstrated anti-tumor efficacy in a mouse melanoma lung metastasis model. Overall, MACE offers a simple, scalable and effective way of activating NK cells and represents an attractive platform to improve efficacy of NK therapy.

Delete 10 words or phrases from the following paragraph that don't contribute much to its meaning, but keep readability:
"We screened various antibodies for MACE functionalization to optimize their adhesion to NK cells, including the clinically relevant NK-92 cell line, primary human NK cells from peripheral blood, and primary mouse NK cells. Adhesion was evaluated by measuring the percentage of cell population binding to at least a single MACE. Antibody-modified MACE were able to adhere to the NK cell surface and were stably integrated with the cell membrane. Interestingly, only few antibodies could effectively mediate adhesion. We selected anti-CD45 as a targeting antibody due to its stable expression on lymphocytes and good adhesion efficiency with 46.6% of cells having at least one attached MACE. MACE without antibody functionalization did not adhere to NK cells whereas anti-CD45 antibody-modified MACE adhered efficiently to all the tested NK cells. Adhesion could be further tuned by modulating MACE to cell ratio. We also verified that the addition of an antibody targeting NK activating receptors to MACE – NKp30 in case of NK-92 and NKp46 in case of mouse NK cells – did not negatively impact adhesion. Surprisingly, the addition of activating antibodies alone was not enough to mediate good adhesion. MACE adhesion was stable and resistant to detachment upon encountering physiologically relevant shear stresses."
